main event: A pilot at Manston AFS, England, observed an unidentified flying object on January 10, 1951.
interesting points: The observation lasted for about 5 to 6 minutes,The object was measured at an estimated altitude of 60,000 feet,Conclusions were made that it could possibly be a balloon or an aircraft but was considered unidentified,The object was described as saucer-shaped and silver in color,The pilot was fully trained and the sighting was confirmed by staff on duty.
